-- Italy Treasury asks banks to prepare new inflation-linked BTPEI
-- 
-- Tue Mar 11, 2014 07:12AM EDT
-- None



ROME, March 11 (Reuters) - Italy's Treasury on Tuesday asked five banks to prepare the sale of a new 10-year BTPEI, a bond linked to the euro zone inflation rate, a statement said.

The Treasury said the sale would take place "in the near future" without specifying exactly when.